## Phase 0 — Prerequisites ✅

- DNS CNAMEs `admin` + `api` in Netlify DNS → Railway
- Railway custom domains on Laravel service (port **8080**)

---

## Phase 1 — Backend auth API ✅

Sanctum, `POST /api/login`, CORS, `SESSION_DOMAIN=.indianopinions.com` on Railway.

---

## Phase 2 — Next.js sign-in ✅

`/sign-in` calls `api.indianopinions.com` directly with `credentials: 'include'`.

---

## Phase 3 — DNS + Railway ✅

Railway env documented in `docs/.env-railway.txt`.

---

## Phase 4 — Netlify ✅

No Laravel proxy on public site. `netlify.toml` uses subdomain API/admin URLs.

---

## Phase 5 — Cleanup ✅

- Removed `studio/src/app/api/auth/*`, `auth-proxy.ts`, Netlify/Next Laravel proxies
- Footer Login → `/sign-in`
- Staff URLs → `docs/STAFF.md`

